                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Or_15662-item1">
                     <author ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/no2011123140" key="person_f3362">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Qanawjī, Khalīfah Shāh Muḥammad, active 17th century</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="supplied">قنوجى، خلیفه شاه محمد</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8186">Jāmi‘ al-qavānīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_8186">جامع القوانین</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Collected ornate letters (inshāʾ), also called <title>Inshā-yi Khalīfah</title>, by Khalīfah Shāh Muḥammad. Written while the author was studying at Qannauj, northern India (preface, f. 2r), the work was completed in 1055/1645-6.</p>
                        <p>Comprises four faṣls and a khātimah.</p>
                        <p>Other contents: front inside cover and endpaper, descriptions by former owners (including: ‘M.S. Persan no. 8, Loix, préceptes et formules’), and bookplate of Le Ch. Ferrao de Castelbranco.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
